pacman

Class Executor

  • java.lang.Object
    • pacman.Executor

  • public class Executor
extends java.lang.Object
    This class may be used to execute the game in timed or un-timed modes, with or without visuals. Competitors should implement their controllers in game.entries.ghosts and game.entries.pacman respectively. The skeleton classes are already provided. The package structure should not be changed (although you may create sub-packages in these packages).

      • runExperiment

        public void runExperiment(Controller<Constants.MOVE> pacManController,
                          Controller<java.util.EnumMap<Constants.GHOST,Constants.MOVE>> ghostController,
                          int trials)
        For running multiple games without visuals. This is useful to get a good idea of how well a controller plays against a chosen opponent: the random nature of the game means that performance can vary from game to game. Running many games and looking at the average score (and standard deviation/error) helps to get a better idea of how well the controller is likely to do in the competition.
        Parameters:
        pacManController - The Pac-Man controller
        ghostController - The Ghosts controller
        trials - The number of trials to be executed

      • runGame

        public void runGame(Controller<Constants.MOVE> pacManController,
                    Controller<java.util.EnumMap<Constants.GHOST,Constants.MOVE>> ghostController,
                    boolean visual,
                    int delay)
        Run a game in asynchronous mode: the game waits until a move is returned. In order to slow thing down in case the controllers return very quickly, a time limit can be used. If fasted gameplay is required, this delay should be put as 0.
        Parameters:
        pacManController - The Pac-Man controller
        ghostController - The Ghosts controller
        visual - Indicates whether or not to use visuals
        delay - The delay between time-steps

      • runGameTimed

        public void runGameTimed(Controller<Constants.MOVE> pacManController,
                         Controller<java.util.EnumMap<Constants.GHOST,Constants.MOVE>> ghostController,
                         boolean visual)
        Run the game with time limit (asynchronous mode). This is how it will be done in the competition. Can be played with and without visual display of game states.
        Parameters:
        pacManController - The Pac-Man controller
        ghostController - The Ghosts controller
        visual - Indicates whether or not to use visuals

      • runGameTimedSpeedOptimised

        public void runGameTimedSpeedOptimised(Controller<Constants.MOVE> pacManController,
                                       Controller<java.util.EnumMap<Constants.GHOST,Constants.MOVE>> ghostController,
                                       boolean fixedTime,
                                       boolean visual)
        Run the game in asynchronous mode but proceed as soon as both controllers replied. The time limit still applies so so the game will proceed after 40ms regardless of whether the controllers managed to calculate a turn.
        Parameters:
        pacManController - The Pac-Man controller
        ghostController - The Ghosts controller
        fixedTime - Whether or not to wait until 40ms are up even if both controllers already responded
        visual - Indicates whether or not to use visuals
